	   <tr><td colspan=2>I was thinking of forming a rogue myself, and had a dark-elf nobleman/prissy jerk in mind as a concept (think Lord Steven Regal). Forming up my poison making would be easy I reckon, since I start with the race/class combo that has the most intelligence; and that's good, because I want to do A LOT of different poisons, however... would I ever get my poison components?<br><br>I'd be one of the most hated races in the game, and to get some rare ingredient, I'll have to travel to such goody goody towns as Halas, Freeport, Kelethim (Sp? I meant the dwarf town, for the most advanced poisons) and others to get components. Like, how am I supposed to get into Halas? Then it dawns on me... good races have the mask of the Deceiver: Illusion Dark Elf. Do Dark Elves have anything to cast an illusion of a light race? Hey, we're the real bad guys! We're the REAL assassins! We're the ones who should've thought of that idea... however, I haven't seen any "Mask of the Deceivers for Dark Races" yet.<br><br>But then again, maybe I haven't been looking hard enough.<br><br>If there ain't any such item, I'd like to know if there's any other way for dark elves to enter cities such as Halas and such without being killed by guards. Preferably by doing shady rogue-ish stunts and not hitting tons of goblins/orcs/factionmonsters.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
